Ah, it's comments like this that reaffirm that my writing did its job.



you guys managed to take my worst fear, subvert it, turn it on its head, and make me feel sorry for not wanting to die.
附加记录：    

My first thought when I heard this pitched to me by Othello was , which I love. I adore subversion in articles, and essentially predicating the entire theme on a subversion is like my entire aesthetic. It feels too easy to try to run a grandiose battle predicated on rule of cool for this topic. Sure, that's a good way to take it, and it can feel original if done right, but I love delving into more nuanced themes.

Also, something appeals to me about an end of the world with no explosions, no high octane action, no violence. Just a very peculiar situation, and everyone just have to live with it.1

